The late AmaZulu King Goodwill Zwelithini has been remembered as a man of unity. A special memorial service was held in his honour in KwaNongoma. eNCA's Thulasizwe Simelane has the details. #DStv403​ #eNCA KWANONGOMA - King Goodwill Zwelithini led by example and spoke without fear or favour, according to AmaZulu Prime Minister, Prince Mangosuthu Buthelezi Buthelezi says the King's reign was one of peace. READ: Only God knows who will succeed King Zwelithini, says sister "Leading according to his conscience, what he spoke, he did. When he told us to till our lands and plant our fields, he led by example," said Buthelezi. According to the AmaZulu Prime Minister, the monarch showed great foresight in the gathering storm of economic crisis. AmaZulu Prime Minister, Mangosuthu Buthelezi said King Goodwill Zwelithini led by example and spoke without fear or favour. #DStv403 #RIPKingGoodwillZwelithini pic.twitter.com/7vSKoU8oMJ The House of Traditional Leaders, who also honoured the AmaZulu King at his official memorial service, says the nation can honour the late monarch by ensuring peace in the land. The House has described the King as a fountain of historical knowledge. The House of Traditional Leaders says the nation can honour AmaZulu King Goodwill Zwelithini by making sure there is peace in the land. #DStv403 #RIPKingGoodwillZwelithini #eNCA pic.twitter.com/jodKJ9wiil